The paper proposes a new model for graph classification using a combination of quantum spatial graph convolution and traditional convolutional neural network architecture. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
